#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.62:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.62:0.2"
msgid "6. Upayavagga "
msgstr "6. Involvement "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Niruttipathasutta "
msgstr "62. The Scope of Language "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.62:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Contra BB, the “patha” are not the five aggregates (there’s three of them!) but the three ways of using language, i.e. the three tenses.
msgctxt "sn22.62:1.2"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, niruttipathā adhivacanapathā paññattipathā asaṅkiṇṇā asaṅkiṇṇapubbā, na saṅkīyanti, na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhā samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three scopes of language, terminology, and descriptions. They’re uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’re not being corrupted now, nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:1.3"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "sn22.62:1.4"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ atītaṃ niruddhaṃ vipariṇataṃ ‘ahosī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘ahosī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘ahosī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "When form has passed, ceased, and perished, its designation, label, and description is ‘was’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:1.5"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘is’ or ‘will be’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.62:2.1"
msgid "Yā vedanā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā ‘ahosī’ti tassā saṅkhā, ‘ahosī’ti tassā samaññā, ‘ahosī’ti tassā paññatti; "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:2.2"
msgid "na tassā saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassā saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.62:3.1"
msgid "Yā saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.62:3.2"
msgid "ye saṅkhārā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā ‘ahesun’ti tesaṃ saṅkhā, ‘ahesun’ti tesaṃ samaññā, ‘ahesun’ti tesaṃ paññatti; "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:3.3"
msgid "na tesaṃ saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tesaṃ saṅkhā ‘bhavissantī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.72, sc4
msgctxt "sn22.62:4.1"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ atītaṃ niruddhaṃ vipariṇataṃ, ‘ahosī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘ahosī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘ahosī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "consciousness has passed, ceased, and perished, its designation, label, and description is ‘was’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:4.2"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘is’ or ‘will be’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.62:5.1"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ ajātaṃ apātubhūtaṃ, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "When form is not yet born, and has not yet appeared, its designation, label, and description is ‘will be’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:5.2"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘is’ or ‘was’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.62:6.1"
msgid "Yā vedanā ajātā apātubhūtā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassā saṅkhā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassā samaññā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassā paññatti; "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:6.2"
msgid "na tassā saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassā saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.62:7.1"
msgid "Yā saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.62:7.2"
msgid "ye saṅkhārā ajātā apātubhūtā, ‘bhavissantī’ti tesaṃ saṅkhā, ‘bhavissantī’ti tesaṃ samaññā, ‘bhavissantī’ti tesaṃ paññatti; "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:7.3"
msgid "na tesaṃ saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tesaṃ saṅkhā ‘ahesun’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.62:8.1"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ ajātaṃ apātubhūtaṃ, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘bhavissatī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "consciousness is not yet born, and has not yet appeared, its designation, label, and description is ‘will be’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:8.2"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘atthī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘is’ or ‘was’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.62:9.1"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ jātaṃ pātubhūtaṃ, ‘atthī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘atthī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘atthī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "When form has been born, and has appeared, its designation, label, and description is ‘is’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:9.2"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘was’ or ‘will be’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn22.62:10.1"
msgid "Yā vedanā jātā pātubhūtā, ‘atthī’ti tassā saṅkhā, ‘atthī’ti tassā samaññā, ‘atthī’ti tassā paññatti; "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:10.2"
msgid "na tassā saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti, na tassā saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn22.62:11.1"
msgid "Yā saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.62:11.2"
msgid "ye saṅkhārā jātā pātubhūtā, ‘atthī’ti tesaṃ saṅkhā, ‘atthī’ti tesaṃ samaññā, ‘atthī’ti tesaṃ paññatti; "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.62:11.3"
msgid "na tesaṃ saṅkhā ‘ahesun’ti, na tesaṃ saṅkhā, ‘bhavissantī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn22.62:12.1"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ jātaṃ pātubhūtaṃ, ‘atthī’ti tassa saṅkhā, ‘atthī’ti tassa samaññā, ‘atthī’ti tassa paññatti; "
msgstr "consciousness has been born, and has appeared, its designation, label, and description is ‘is’. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:12.2"
msgid "na tassa saṅkhā ‘ahosī’ti, na tassa saṅkhā ‘bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "It’s not ‘was’ or ‘will be’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.73, sc13
msgctxt "sn22.62:13.1"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo niruttipathā adhivacanapathā paññattipathā asaṃkiṇṇā asaṃkiṇṇapubbā, na saṅkīyanti, na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhā samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "These are the three scopes of language, terminology, and descriptions. They’re uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’re not being corrupted now, nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.62:13.2"
msgid "Yepi te, bhikkhave, ahesuṃ ukkalā vassabhaññā ahetukavādā akiriyavādā natthikavādā, tepime tayo niruttipathe adhivacanapathe paññattipathe na garahitabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ amaññiṃsu. "
msgstr "Even those wanderers of the past, Vassa and Bhañña of Ukkalā, who taught the doctrines of no-cause, inaction, and nihilism, didn’t imagine that these three scopes of language should be criticized or rejected. "

msgctxt "sn22.62:13.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

#. VAR: Nindāghaṭṭanabyārosaupārambhabhayā”ti → nindābyārosaupārambhabhayāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.62:13.4"
msgid "Nindāghaṭṭanabyārosaupārambhabhayā”ti. "
msgstr "For fear of being blamed, criticized, and faulted.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.62:13.5"
msgid "Majjhimapaṇṇāsakassa upayavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn22.62:14.1"
msgid "Upayo bījaṃ udānaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.62:14.2"
msgid "Upādānaparivattaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.62:14.3"
msgid "Sattaṭṭhānañca sambuddho, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.62:14.4"
msgid "Pañcamahāli ādittā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.62:14.5"
msgid "Vaggo niruttipathena cāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
